    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pasta is nearly cooked, chop your <strong>dill</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Once cooked, remove the dish from the oven and add the <strong>spinach</strong>,<strong> double cream</strong> and most of the <strong>chopped dill</strong> (save some for garnish!) and gently stir until the spinach starts to wilt and the fish is cooked through – this is your <strong>one-pot creamy horseradish smoked basa tortiglioni</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
